---
title: Creamy Chimichurri Beef Tenderloin with Rice & Garlicky Roasted Broccoli
description: Creamy, tangy, herbaceous chimichurri sauce takes pork filets to the next level for an easy-yet-impressive meal. You'll spoon it over juicy roasted pork and serve it alongside savory, garlicky broccoli and fluffy, buttery rice for a dish that's as flavor-packed as it is easy to make.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67ceaf8cfc617b70a129fded-7db62b20.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67d007daceae9743fd559e33-en-US.pdf
time required: 35m
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-chimichurri-beef-tenderloin-67d007daceae9743fd559e33
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 490 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry @Broccoli{1}. Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Pat pork dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt, and @Pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%oz} and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}. (For 4 servings, spread pork out across entire sheet.)

-- Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook until chicken is browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or until beef reaches desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board to rest.

On opposite side of sheet from pork, toss broccoli with a drizzle of oil, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss broccoli on a second baking sheet.)

Roast on top rack until pork is cooked through and broccoli is browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}. (For 4, roast broccoli on top rack and pork on middle rack, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

Transfer pork to a cutting board to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

On the opposite side of the sheet, toss broccoli with a drizzle of oil, remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss broccoli on a second baking sheet.)

> Skip roasting chicken or beef. Spread broccoli across entire sheet.

While pork and broccoli roast, in a small #bowl{}, combine @Chimichurri{2%oz} and @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}.

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Divide rice and broccoli between plates in separate sections. Top rice with pork; spoon creamy chimichurri over pork. Serve.

> Slice chicken or beef against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.